│ Based on the root cause analysis, the crash occurs in        │
│ `BoUpSLP::getTreeCost` when it tries to calculate the cost   │
│ of vectorizing a cast instruction that is already a vector   │
│ operation. This happens during cost modeling for horizontal  │
│ reductions, where a vector `zext` is treated as a scalar     │
│ instruction in the SLP tree.                                 │
│                                                              │
│ The `getTreeCost` function attempts to create a "vector of   │
│ vectors" type by calling `getWidenedType` on an              │
│ already-vector type, which leads to an assertion failure in  │
│ the target-specific `getCastInstrCost` implementation.       │
│                                                              │
│ To fix this, I will modify `BoUpSLP::getTreeCost` to detect  │
│ this special case. When costing a cast operation, if the     │
│ destination type (`DstTy`) is already a vector, we should    │
│ use the source and destination types directly for the cost   │
│ calculation instead of trying to widen them further. This    │
│ correctly models the cost of a single vector cast            │
│ instruction, which is what the horizontal reduction analysis │
│ intended.                                                    │
│                                                              │
│ I will now apply this change.                                │
│                                                              │
